'''Wesley Arrington Witherspoon''' (born January 27, 1990) is an American [[basketball]] player.

He played [[college basketball]] for the [[University of Memphis]] [[Memphis Tigers men's basketball|Tigers]].<ref name="Memphis Tigers - Memphis Tigers men's basketball - 11  Wesley Witherspoon">{{cite web|url=http://www.gotigersgo.com/sports/m-baskbl/mtt/witherspoon_wesley00.html|title=11  Wesley Witherspoon|publisher=[[Memphis Tigers]]|accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>

He was on the [[San Antonio Spurs]] roster, but did not play a game for them.<ref name="Yahoo! Sports -  Wesley Witherspoon #11, GF, San Antonio">{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/nba/players/5125/|title= Wesley Witherspoon #11, GF, San Antonio|work=[[Yahoo! Sports]]|publisher=[[Yahoo]]|accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref><ref name="CBS Sports - 11 Wesley Witherspoon">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbssports.com/nba/players/playerpage/2020547/wesley-witherspoon|title=11 Wesley Witherspoon|work=[[CBS Sports]]|publisher=[[CBS Corporation]]|accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>
 
In 2014, Witherspoon was picked to play for the [[Air21 Express]] of the [[Philippine Basketball Association]].<ref name="The Philippine Star - 19 March 2014 - Air21 taps Witherspoon as new import">{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/sports/2014/03/19/1303046/air21-taps-witherspoon-new-import|title=Air21 taps Witherspoon as new import|last=Beltran|first=Nelson|date=19 March 2014|work=[[The Philippine Star]]|accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>

Witherspoon was signed for [[Helsinki Seagulls]] in September 2014 to play in [[Korisliiga]], the top tier of Finnish basketball. Also rated in the top 100 shooters in the world for players 6'9" or above.<ref name= "Wesley Witherspoon liittyy Helsinki Seagullsin miehistöön">{{cite news|url=http://www.basket.fi/uutiset/?x22026=26227575|title=Wesley Witherspoon liittyy Helsinki Seagullsin miehistöön|date=24 September 2014|accessdate=25 September 2014|work=[[Finnish Basketball Association]]|language=fi}}</ref>

==The Basketball Tournament==
Wesley Witherspoon played for Team Memphis State in the [[The Basketball Tournament 2018|2018]] edition of [[The Basketball Tournament]]. He averaged 7.0 points per game, 1.5 rebounds per game and 1.0 assists per game. Team Memphis State reached the second round before falling to Team DRC.

